<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1060,1339]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[215,536,1169,1194]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Comparative morphology.</emphasis>
The goal of this work is not to discuss the geographical variations of the Japanese subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[415,631,1206,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Ceruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignarius">
<emphasis box="[415,631,1206,1230]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ceruchus lignarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, therefore the three subspecies are not treated separately. All characters investigated are applicable to all the three subspecies. 
<taxonomicName box="[817,1039,1242,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Ceruchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lignarius">
<emphasis box="[817,1039,1242,1266]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ceruchus lignarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses at least eight peculiar characters (
<tableCitation box="[279,405,1278,1302]" captionStart-0="TABLE 1" captionStart-1="TABLE 2" captionStartId-0="5.[151,239,151,175]" captionStartId-1="7.[151,239,151,175]" captionText-0="TABLE 1. Summary of male characters of Ceruchus species from China and Japan (Abbreviations: li = Ceruchus lignarius; l = Ceruchus luojishanensis; m = Ceruchus minor; d = Ceruchus deuvei; k = Ceruchus katerinae; y = Ceruchus yangi; r = Ceruchus reginae; n = Ceruchus niger; s = Ceruchus sinensis; t = Ceruchus tabanai)." captionText-1="TABLE 2. Summary of female characters of Ceruchus species from China and Japan (Abbreviations: li = Ceruchus lignarius; l = Ceruchus luojishanensis; m = Ceruchus minor; d = Ceruchus deuvei; k = Ceruchus katerinae; y = Ceruchus yangi; r = Ceruchus reginae; n = Ceruchus niger; s = Ceruchus sinensis; t = Ceruchus tabanai)." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Tables 
<number box="[361,405,1278,1302]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</tableCitation>
), which are not shared by any Chinese species.
</paragraph>
